The paper discusses a new multiple access technique for wireless networks, which involves mapping different data streams to codewords of multi-dimensional cookbooks. This technique is designed to improve spectral efficiency and link-adaptation in heavily loaded networks. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Communications (cs.COMM), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories of arXiv CS.
